Business Brief -- Blockbuster Entertainment Corp.:
   Franchisee Files Complaint
   Chain Calls `Without Merit'
The franchisee, which operates under the names Capitol
Entertainment of Northern Virginia Ltd., Capitol
Entertainment of Prince William County Inc. and Capitol
Entertainment of Montgomery County Inc., owns 28 Blockbuster
Superstores.
   The franchisee said it is seeking more than $40 million in
actual damages and $100 million in punitive damages for
breach of contract, breach of fiduciary duty and unfair
competition.
   In a statement yesterday, Blockbuster said its acquisition
was "expressly within the company's rights under its various
agreements with Capitol Entertainment."